> Beans! Beans! They're not just good for your heart. These beans are so full of
> delicious dynamic flavors, they're practically a work of art. The filling in
> this casserole has borlotti beans and green pepper simmered in Southwestern
> spices and chipotle chili. It gets wedged between two layers of tortillas,
> topped with cheese, and baked in the oven until piping hot. And when it comes
> out all hot, melty, and steamy, all that's left to do is add a drizzle of
> crema to cool things off.

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Lightly oil an
#8-by-8-inch baking dish{}. Halve, core, and seed @long green pepper{1%unit},
then cut into small squares. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2%unit},
separating greens and whites. Halve and core @roma tomato{1%unit}, then cut into
small cubes. Drain and rinse @borlotti beans{13.4%ounce}.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in a #medium pot{} over
medium-high heat. Add green pepper and scallion whites. Cook, tossing, until
tender, about ~{5%minutes}. Season with @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon},
@chili powder{1/4%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

> TIP: Add more chipotle for extra heat, but save some for the crema.

Stir @tomato paste{3%tablespoon} into pot (we sent more). Let cook for about
~{1%minute}. Stir in beans and @water{3/4%cup}. Let simmer until slightly
thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Arrange three @corn tortillas{6%unit} in a single layer on the bottom of your
oiled #baking dish{}, cutting one tortilla in half to fit. Add all of the bean
mixture to dish and spread out evenly. Layer remaining tortillas on top, again
cutting one in half to fit. Gently press down on tortillas to remove any air
pockets. Scatter @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup} over top. Cover dish with
#aluminum foil{}. Bake in oven until filling is hot and cheese melts,
~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, stir together @sour cream{2%tablespoon},
@water{1%tablespoon}, @?chili powder{remaining}, and @hot sauce{1%teaspoon}.
Season with @salt{}.

Once casserole is done baking, remove from oven and let rest ~{5%minutes}. Cut
into four squares and divide between plates. Drizzle crema over top. Garnish
with scallion greens and tomatoes and serve.